wiki_detail.notes:
* If '''Rumble''' lands a Harpoon on a target that already has a stack of magic resistance reduction while in {{ai|Junkyard Titan 2|Rumble|Danger Zone}}, it will increase the reduction from this first stack to the enhanced amount, as well.
* A buff with the magic resistance reduction tooltip is applied to {{tip|minions}} and {{tip|pets}}, but their magic resistance is unaffected by ''Electro Harpoon''.{{bug}}
* Each ''Electro Harpoon'' cast triggers {{tip|Spellblade}} and stacks {{ai|Force Pulse|Kassadin}}.
* ''Electro Harpoon's'' missile will fail to fire if '''Rumble''' is {{tip|suppression|suppressed}} during the cast time.{{bug|2}}
{{Effect at cast time end}}
* '''Rumble''' stocks an ''Electro Harpoon'' charge before the ability is even learned.

* A static target standing where the missiles first impact may take an extra tick of damage (11 ticks), while a static target standing at the end of the trail may take one fewer tick (9 ticks).{{bug}}
* ''The Equalizer's'' hitbox consists of a row of rockets with a circular damage hitbox each. The radius of each is 205 units, and rockets drop at a distance of 180 units between one another when ''The Equalizer'' is cast. 
** The missile that manages the rockets being deployed starts 150 units behind the target vector origin, and thus drops the first rocket at 30 units in front of the cast vector origin after {{rutngt|0.1125}}.
** The rockets are intended to not deal damage for the first {{fd|0.25}} seconds. Due to a bug, this becomes {{fd|0.25}}-{{fd|0.5}} seconds 'at random'.
*** If Rumble dies while ''The Equalizer'' is just cast, this buff will be removed by death and the area of effect will start dealing damage sooner.{{bug}}
